{"id":13582,"date":"2020-08-20T21:37:55","date_gmt":"2020-08-21T04:37:55","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/?p=13582"},"modified":"2024-01-09T11:25:23","modified_gmt":"2024-01-09T19:25:23","slug":"twin-peaks-pot-hill2","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2020\/08\/20\/twin-peaks-pot-hill2\/","title":{"rendered":"TWIN PEAKS (Pot Hill)"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><em><strong>TWIN PEAKS\u00a0 <\/strong><\/em>2119m &amp; 2150m<em><br \/>\nThis off-trail, alpine hike goes over two bumps on the ridge line between Grassy and Siwash mountains in the Bonnington Range. There is one km of ridge between them. The common name for these is Pot Hill.\u00a0<\/em>\u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong><br \/>\nRating:\u00a0\u2666\u2666\u2666\u25ca\u25ca<br \/>\n<\/strong><strong>Location:<\/strong> Bonnington Range between Castlegar and Salmo.\u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Difficulty:<\/strong> A1 Easy <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Elevation Gain:<\/strong> +333m<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Key Elevations<\/strong>: Munson FSR 1820m; Peak #2 2150m<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Distance:<\/strong> 4.6kms <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Time:<\/strong> 3 hours <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Season:<\/strong> July through October <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Access:<\/strong> Good gravel FSR &#8211; 2WD low clearance <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Map:<\/strong> 82F\/5\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Drive:<\/strong> Drive to the summit of the Bombi summit on Highway 3 between Castlegar and Salmo. Turn north onto Munson Forest Service Road. Drive 13.7kms staying on the main road at all junctions. Park at the pullout. <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>0.0<\/strong>km. Start of Munson FSR<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">2.5kms. Left on main road <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">3.5kms. Right. 3.6kms &#8211; left. 3.7kms &#8211; right. 4.5kms \u2013 right, always on main road. <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">6.0kms. Left. Grassy Mt appears ahead. 6.1kms \u2013 left. <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">10.4kms. Right. 12.7kms \u2013 right. 13kms \u2013 switchback right. Ignore the cairns on the side of the road. <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">13.7kms. Park in pullout on right<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Route:<\/strong> There is no trail. Cross the road and ascend the rough quad track that ascends part way, with cairns and intermittent trail to the first peak. At .4km, leave the track at a pink flag. Follow cairns through grassy meadows on the ridge line. Grassy Mt is to the south.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">1.3kms reach the top of Peak #1 &#8211; 2119m (225m ascent). Follow the ridge for 1km.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">2.3kms reach the top of Peak #2. \u2013 2150m. Siwash is visible to the north east.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Return the same way.<\/span><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>TWIN PEAKS\u00a0 2119m &amp; 2150m This off-tr